    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-bfd-unsolicited-09.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-bfd-unsolicited-09.txt</link>
        <title>"Unsolicited BFD for Sessionless Applications", Enke Chen, Naiming Shen, Robert Raszuk, Reshad Rahman</title>
        <dc:date>2021-12-03T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>For operational simplification of "sessionless" applications using BFD, in this document we present procedures for "unsolicited BFD" that allow a BFD session to be initiated by only one side, and be established without explicit per-session configuration or registration by the other side (subject to certain per-interface or per-router policies).  We also introduce a new YANG module to configure and manage "unsolicited BFD".  The YANG module in this document conforms to the Network Management Datastore Architecture (NMDA) [RFC8342].</description>
    </item>
